        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:41AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 741 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Quail, or 16 miles north of Memphis, moving
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lutie, Hedley, Dozier, Quail, Samnorwood, Dodson, and Wellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
